en_352023_0	Major General B P S de Silva took office as the 13th General Officer Commanding (GOC) of the 57 Division under the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi on Monday (2).
en_352023_1	The newly-appointed GOC was greeted to a formal Guard Turnout honour at the entrance to the 57 Division Headquarters upon his arrival.
en_352023_2	Afterwards, 7 Sri Lanka Light Infantry troops saluted him in a Guard of Honour as a military formality.
en_352023_3	Afterwards, members of the Maha Sangha blessed the new office chanting ‘Seth Pirith’ as the new GOC, Major General B P S de Silva placed his signature in an official document to signify the acceptance of the new office.
en_352023_4	Later on, he addressed all Officers and Other Ranks serving the 57 Division areas.
en_352023_5	All troops under command to Brigades and Battalions were there at the Utility Building of the 57 Division to listen to him.
en_352023_6	Finally, refreshments for all ranks brought the event to end.
en_352023_7	All Brigade Commanders, Commanding Officers, Senior Officers, Officers and Other Ranks attended the event.
